reviews.review:
Dead by Daylight is a strange game. It also fills alone the whole genre of the horror asymmetrical games. It can be sometimes really frustrating and less than in the past, sometimes you can meet toxic players, but it happens rarely and if you are able to shrug shoulders, you will have tons of fun. 

[h1] PRO[/h1]
+ really fun played with friends as survivors;
+ interesting mechanics:
+ good variety of characters (a lot from official licenses) and a lot of perks to choose from while you grow in level ;
+ for horror fans;
+ play in team as surv or alone as killer, both format are fun;

[h1] CONS[/h1]
- sometimes you can meet really toxic disturbed players; 
- some balance problems, not all the killers are created equally good;
- some killer's build are boring to play against;
-- devs are present but sometimes they fix the wrong things;
--- devs are present but unfortunately some of 'em are just childish morons;
---- gotta face console killers, simply toxic garbage players for the most;
